"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-02-paris-2024-olympics-waldrum-provides-reason-for-super-falcons-poor-outing\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons head coach, Randy Waldrum has suggested that better preparation could have helped his side at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The former African champions failed to make it beyond the group stage in the women's football event losing all three games.  The Super Falcons spent two weeks in Sevilla, Spain before the start of the competition.  The West Africans also lost 1-0 to Canada in their only friendly before the Olympics.  Waldrum said things would have been different for his side if they had spend more time in camp.  \\\"We prepared for them [all three opponents] based on the fact that we have not had a lot of time,\\\" the American was quoted by ESPN.  \\\"We missed the last window before the Olympics and so we missed 10 days of good training before the Olympics.\\\"  Ayemnwere leaves Sporting Lagos for Ikorodu City  EPL: Former Leicester City manager, Shakespeare is dead  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"